<br><i>No matter where you go or who you're with, put enough people in a room and they will inevitably find something to quibble over.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 7:01:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1139.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More:</span><hr size=1> Oh man, I remember my first enchanter and when I thought humans got an EXP bonus, and that the illusion would give me that EXP bonus. A few people told me I was on crack, but I kept saying, &quot;Better safe than sorry.&quot; :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 7:14:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1139.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> IIRC, halflings ..</span><hr size=1> .. still get their bonus.  Only the racial penalties were removed.  You should have been using &quot;illusion: short and furry&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukhromalok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khromalok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 3:26:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1139.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IIRC, halflings ..</span><hr size=1> Yes, Halflings get the experience bonus.  Many believe that this was a mistake on Verant's part and that the experience bonus was really suppose to go to Humans as is stated in the different EQ player guides.  But since Verant is terrible at admitting their mistakes, they just kept the experience bonus on the Halflings.  Halflings receive racial Hide, Sneak, and Infravision, and on top of this they receive an experience bonus?  Nah, Humans were suppose to receive the experience bonus, not Halflings.<br>
<br>
And only the class based penalties were removed a while back (ie Hybrid and Monk penalties).  Trolls and Iksars still have a 20% racial experience penalty in place.<br>
<br>
Khromalok tha Despised <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubraellarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 4:47:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1139.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IIRC, halflings ..</span><hr size=1> Class based exp penaltys were a pain, shame i dont have the link.. but a troll shadowkight at say lv30.. needed around the same exp as a lv35 warrior of standard race. (rougly, cant remember exact figures... but kinda crazy)<br>
<br>
But then again it was not that bad, a shadowknights etc had same hp as warriors... so payed the penalty for there spells, dual wield and lack of kick, then again dual wield was not a factor as at the time the 2 handed wepons scaled with dual wield.<br>
<br>
Wont go into how that changed the tables...<br>
<br>
Anyways, the exp penaltys are still there just offset by magical chunks of exp that attatche themselfs to the hybrids to offset this.<br>
<br>
Sounds wierd but this still didnt totally fix the exp penalty, as classes that had no penalty also got these chunks of exp lol... though i am not a great deal worried about it, since it does help me keep my lv with friends, the problem before was that we used to lag behind.<br>
Well, as a shadowknight my exp bonus solo and in group is different, i get more exp per kill solo due to bonus to offset this evil penalty, though an efficent group is always faster... we dont do that badly solo as you might think.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 7:56:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1139.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/hand.gif height=42 width=42></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: IIRC, halflings ..</span><hr size=1> The hybrid experience penalty was always insane.  There's really no rationalizing it, which is why Verant decided to eventually remove it, despite making &quot;hell freezing over&quot;-like comments that it would never be changed.<br>
<br>
It's true that a shadow knight is more powerful/versatile/whatever than a like-level warrior in many situations.  However, experience-wise, as a troll shadow knight nears the end of hell level 35, a human or wood elven warrior (who has gained the same amount of experience) would be approaching <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> level 43</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  And what this essentially means is that a level 35 troll shadow knight would be sucking up just as much experience in a group as a level 42 warrior.  The disparity there is pretty gross and is one reason why many people would hesitate to group with hybrids, especially hybrids with race penalties on top of their class penalty. <p><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT><BR>
